The entry date will be the date when the effect is executed.
The key field is mandatory and enables special entry localization. You will be able to access the character and the specified variables when localizing it.
Variables only support objects, not values.
scope:situation = {
record_situation_special_event = {
key = special_event_key
actor = scope:character (optional)
phase = situation_phase_type_key (optional)
variables = {
other_character = scope:other_character
title = scope:title
}
}
}

Can be retrieved with situation_center_province link.
scope:situation = {
set_situation_center_province = province
}

If a target province is specified, the catalyst will only trigger in that subregion.
scope:situation = {
trigger_situation_catalyst = {
catalyst = catalyst_type
character = scope:character (optional, the actor who will trigger the catalyst)
county = scope:province (optional, identifies the subregion where the catalyst will trigger)
}
}
simplified: activate_situation_catalyst = <catalyst_type>
example: activate_situation_catalyst = situation_catalyst_type:war_started

